=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Discussion on Vox rotation....</span><hr size=1> (This thread was originally entitled &quot;UNB, please read&quot; in reference to United Norrathian Brigade's inability to get their vox raid together on 48 hours notice due to real life issues.  It begins with my reply to a request by them to have their deadline extended by 24 hours.  The thread has now evolved into something of a discussion of the rules for timeframe in taking down vox, so I've moved it to raids: discussion.)<br>
<br>
Sorry guys.  While I respect your real life issues, my only duty here is as a maintainer of the lists.  I don't really make or judge the rules, I just enforce them.  Because of that, I'm not at liberty to allow anyone to delay their raid or push back a few days.  I hope you understand this.  <br>
<br>
I'm forced to show you guys as passing.  Good luck in the future.  If you need to discuss this with me, please contact me in game. <p><BR>
Zestrenocya Zephryfyst, the happiest taxi driver in Norrath <BR>
Proud member of Silent Redemption <BR>
Proprietor: Norrath's Finest Taxi Service <BR>
<A HREF="http://sr.amiga.tm/" TARGET="_new"><IMG ALT="Silent Redemption Member" BORDER=0 SRC="http://fairblade.sinbad.net/images/SRlogo.gif"></A>


</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzestrenocya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zestrenocya</A> at: 1/24/01 3:05:17 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uganaddor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ganaddor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/23/01 7:40:02 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/G36206?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: UNB -- please read</span><hr size=1> Zest, I am ok with this. However I want to add it is not easy to get sufficient sign up in 48 hours even I posted my intention just after Pawn of Prophecy posting the result. If rotation is moving fast with a lot of failed raids because raid organisers have only 48 hours to prepare it is no good. I may ask to change this rule if Vox raids fail continuously.<br>
<br>
I have no intention to break this rule and I respect you to forced us to cancel. <p>Ganaddor Saolinlight<BR>
Lvl 52 disciple of the Shaolin Temple<BR>
<BR>
Dikamin Serilisknight<BR>
Semi-Retired 51th Paladin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucamala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Camala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/23/01 10:55:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: UNB -- please read</span><hr size=1> the 48 hours rule is not at all constructive - old world dragon raids in the past (i've been at many of them) all had the problem that not enough people came - about 50% of them failed. it does not help us to have a higher number of tries to kill them if also a higher percentage of this tries fail. and in cases like this very special one, vox would have been killed sooner if you accepted the one day delay instead of letting it do the next one on the list.<br>
<br>
maybe its different for higher lvl dragons (never been on such a raid) but for low lvl dragons it would be better to allow people more time to organise the raids and have more successful ones - just my thoughts<br>
<br>
there have also been raids in the past where the raid failed and same guild gave it another try the next day thus violating the 48 hours rule and no one complained, no need to be so strict here - and you also did not delete their posts here.... <p>Camala<BR>
Gemchopper<BR>
Warriors of Wrath<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzestrenocya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zestrenocya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Norrath's Finest Taxi Service</span><br>  Posts: 819<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/23/01 1:09:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: UNB -- please read</span><hr size=1> Guys....<br>
<br>
Just a suggestion here....but I definitely won't delete a post that says &quot;MY GUILD UP FOR VOX IN A WEEK OR SO -- sign up here if youre interested in going.&quot;  I mean, I might delete that post if you aren't in say...the top four or five, but if you're second, I would expect you'd have some sort of preliminary sign up thread here long before the previous raid fails or succeeds.<br>
<br>
Of course, some people will post &quot;I would like to be included, but I can only play on weekends&quot; or something like that, but at least you have a list of maybe 25 names to start with before your turn even begins.  If even half of those 25 names can make your raid, whenever it is, you're off to a good start.  I saw how many sign ups UNB got in only 24 hours.<br>
<br>
The rules for raid organization even suggest that it be done this way.  I'm sorry for the time limitations.  All I can say is, that's what the server voted for.  I'd love to just change the rules arbitrarily whenever I find something isn't working well, but I'm not empowered to do that. <p><BR>
