Proprietor: Norrath's Finest Taxi Service <BR>
<A HREF="http://sr.amiga.tm/" TARGET="_new"><IMG ALT="Silent Redemption Member" BORDER=0 SRC="http://fairblade.sinbad.net/images/SRlogo.gif"></A>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualannia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alannia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Talaena's Tang</span><br>  Posts: 483<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/23/01 3:07:21 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/alannia2000/sqeeze.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: UNB -- please read</span><hr size=1> Bear with me, I'm &quot;new&quot;. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   well sort of anyways.<br>
<br>
Zesty, first off, you guys are doing a great job at helping keep us organized.  You're role or decision I don't think are in question here.  UNB had to pass based on the rules that were set up way back when, and that's understood.  The fact that the Brell server even HAS people willing to help with the rotation is commendable of itself.<br>
<br>
What I'm wondering is whether or not a new vote is in order.  The server is changing, and a new and different breed of people are coming to (and leaving!) the appropriate level for the old world dragons.  And it's true, Vox is living far more often than she is dying.<br>
<br>
I personally didn't sign up for Vox or Naggy because of the variances in when these raids occur.  I only have a few weeknights, and weekends to play with, and with an up-in-the-air raid time like these dragons tend to be, its hard to commit to something without knowing for sure that I can be there.  I'm from the old school, where you don't say you're going to be somewhere unless you're sure. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I guess all I really mean by this is that just because there's not a lot of sign ups doesn't mean there won't be a lot of people available and willing to help out.  UNB, as an example, was enlisting aid from other guilds, The Combine Alliance, I know for sure.  Several there would have helped, time permitting.<br>
<br>
To keep this as short as I can, in conclussion, I agree with a lot of what Camala stated.  If a new vote needs to be issued to get the rules changed, then a new vote needs to be issued, and if we're in the minority, so be it!  The people coming into the old world dragon raids are not always as experienced in raid leading as they were even two months ago.<br>
<br>
All I can say for sure is that Vox has not been falling.  Prep time is key.  And as I'm sure we all can relate to, we don't all fall under Verant's vision of &quot;have no RL life, or you won't succeed.&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   In summary, I'd rather see more Vox's dead and her loot table safely in the hands of various Brell members than more Vox raid signups per month.<br>
<br>
Sorry!  I don't know for sure if this belongs here or in discussion, or somewhere else entirely, so if I've posted somewhere that I shouldn't, please feel free to move or delete the post.  I apologize most humbly if I've posted incorrectly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaennenfizzlewhiff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaennen Fizzlewhiff</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 331<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/23/01 4:40:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: UNB -- please read</span><hr size=1> We've all seen how no shows are dragged through the mud on the rants boards and thus ruining peoples chances for future raids.  I don't see why anyone would want to take this risk by signing up for a raid before a definate date is known.  <br>
<br>
I think Vox should be monitored and if enough raid leaders are seeing a problem with finding support then perhaps a revote should take place. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uganaddor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ganaddor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/23/01 10:45:04 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/G36206?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: UNB -- please read</span><hr size=1> Raid discussion may be the better place to discuss this but since everyone replies here I reply here as well.<br>
<br>
I actually have no trouble with Zesty, I will do the same if I were him to enforce the rule. However what I think is this 48 hour limit must be changed.<br>
<br>
Back in many months ago when there were no time limit of attempting dragons some guilds didn't even post anything for over a week when their turns were up. The next one in rotation ended up waiting there for over a week or 2 just for the No. 1 to say something to pass. Dikamin suggested at that time that the raid organisers must post their intention (it's intention, not attempt) within 48 hours and most people suggested to be 72 hours of posting intention and this guideline was used when Chingon was the moderator. The new set of rules has been passed earlier that made the 48 hour limit.<br>
<br>
I suggest this should be 48 hours to post intention, not attempting. Time limit for attempting may be 5 days or so if previous raid failed as this was the approximately the average no. of days to attempt Naggy and Vox previously after a failed raid. Most Vox/Naggy raid organisers can't even get more than half from their guilds as opposed to Trakanon and VS.<br>
<br>
For me I am not going to be included in the rotation again as I can't say for certain I can do a raid within a 48 hour period and I don't know the days ATM. And I have told myself I won't sign up on any dragon raid that appeared to be insufficient preparation. <p>Ganaddor Saolinlight<BR>
Lvl 52 disciple of the Shaolin Temple<BR>
<BR>
Dikamin Serilisknight<BR>
Semi-Retired 51th Paladin</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uganaddor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ganaddor</A> at: 1/23/01 9:49:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukroscloudwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kros Cloudwalker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 97<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/24/01 12:18:53 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cityscope.net/~jackp/jack/kros.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: UNB -- please read</span><hr size=1> This seems to cater, once again, to the larger guilds who have tons of player resources to call upon. A small guild or novice raid leader simply can't round up the personel needed for a difficult raid that quickly.<br>
<br>
Many in our guild are over the 52 limit. That creates problems. Many people in our guild were working diligently to make 45 so they could resonably contribute to the raid if they attended. Our small guild also has some class deficiencies that we must fill in order to even have a chance at defeating VOX.<br>
<br>
But it came up so fast and we were so rushed that we simply could not muster the people needed to do it.<br>
<br>
This event has contributed to my decision to look elsewere for my addictive entertainment. The concept of needing mass quantities of people to kill a dragon is as it should be. Unfortunately, the limitations placed on who can assist based on level, skills, and time constraints IMHO simply takes the fun out of raiding. <br>
<br>
For my freinds who are not so jaded toward EQ though, I ask that the Brell community reconsider its guidelines. Other ervers don't seem to have near as much trouble taking VOX down as ours does. Why is that? <p>Kros Cloudwalker,
Ranger of Karana,
Master Fletcher, Master Brewer,Council Elder of United Norrathian Brotherhood
<BR> <BR> Fazlazen Psychmaster, Enchanter of Prexus, Master Jeweler.
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukreonknitewind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kreon Knitewind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/24/01 3:42:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: UNB -- please read</span><hr size=1> This should be moved to the Raid discussion forum i believe <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  But since the thread has started, here's my 2 cents.....<br>
<br>
Vox has a one week spawn rate, so in essence you have one week and 48 hrs to get your raid organized.  I DO realize this is shortened when a raid fails, the next raiders in line only have 2 days to get organized then.  But I have also been apart of a successful raid on less than 12 hrs notice.  No shows tend to be the biggest problem IMO.  Raid leaders can not prepare properly if people are just signing hoping they can make it, but not really sure whether or not they can.  I think if we can get vox to fall, things will smooth out a bit and we will see a longer string of victories than we have as of late.<br>
<br>
Then again, this is just my opinion, I could be wrong.<br>
<br>
Sir Knitewind  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unillon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nillon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>GD RPers</span><br>  Posts: 1587<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/24/01 5:39:24 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/soj/nillon.jpg height=306 width=162></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion on Vox rotation....</span><hr size=1> I'll tell you exactly why this server has problems killing Vox. All the experienced people who could kill vox easily are 52+, a ton of people signed up who have no business being on the list, therefore whenever a Vox raid fails, it ends up giving the next raid not enough time to plan. IMO the answer is clear up all the redundant raids, put Vox under Adun's system so only the serious Vox raiders will remain. <p>nillon<br>
60 warlord<br>
<a href ="http://sr.amiga.tm">Silent Redemption</a><br>
Champion of Brell <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadunofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adun of Brell</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch!</span><br>  Posts: 904<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/24/01 8:48:49 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/fenye.jpg width=92 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion on Vox rotation....</span><hr size=1> Burn me at the stake for not catering to the little guy, but my opinion is if you can't put together the forces to kill Vox, you shouldn't be on the list.<br>
<br>
There are 3 Darkguard members that are still at L52 so they can do dragon raids.  They've been on a number of Vox raids recently.<br>
<br>
THE RAID LEADERS DIDN'T HAVE A CLUE.  They didn't know how to run a Vox Raid.  They didn't know that you can't stun Vox to interrupt CH.  They weren't mana draining.  They had too many people of insufficient level.<br>
<br>
How long is the stupid list anyways?  If all of the guilds on the list are too small to muster the proper forces to kill Vox, then perhaps some of the guilds should combine forces?<br>
<br>
Hint: You can buff your raiders with L60 Buffs.  Tanks with Aegolism, Rune 5, Shissar, Focus, Circle Resist spells. . . There's tremendous advantage here.<br>
<br>
Adun's only a sliver into 53.  If the damn Vox list wasn't a mile long, I'd sac Adun &amp; run a raid.  Unfortunately, becuase there's so much dead weight (guilds that aren't active, guilds that are all over 52 now, guilds that never had the numbers, but just signed up to get a spot on the list. . .) on the Vox list, it's not worth my time.<br>
<br>
Vox isn't a 12 hour raid.  It's something you can easily do on a weeknight.  It shouldn't be that hard to get the required numbers together. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune.jpg" width="315" height="200"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukruuunch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kruuunch</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ugliest Paladin o' Kaladim</span><br>  Posts: 1301<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/24/01 9:15:05 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.krunch.net/kruunch-face.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion on Vox rotation....</span><hr size=1> I'm a big proponent of smaller guilds raiding dragons (Nag and Vox specifically) but to be perfectly frank, it wouldn't matter to MOST of the failed Vox raids if you gave them 2 weeks to plan the raid. They still would of failed.<br>
<br>
Let me give you a for instance....<br>
<br>
Guild X hosted a Vox raid last week. Two Spiritslammers signed up to go on it. They were both casters. At the raid (not before) they were told that casters wouldn't be able to roll on a white dragon scale (only bards could for their epics). That raid had two nukers; a mage and a wizard. But it had 5 bards (one of them 32nd level). Given these facts (both the &quot;on-the-spot&quot; loot rule and lack of appropriate classes and levels) our guys promptly withdrew.<br>
<br>
THIS HAS BEEN COMMONPLACE!<br>
<br>
