If only experienced raid leaders should be able to lead raid, then Vox, Naggy or any other &quot;raid&quot; mob would never have been killed.  The only way to become a sucessful raid leader is to have done it.  The first people to do it had no experience.  Who is anyone to say who should be able to or not be able to lead a raid?  So much for trying new ways.<br>
<br>
I feel it safe to say that Adun is a good Fear puller.  I bet that he was not a good Fear puller the first time he went there.  He learned by doing.  I was on the raid when he tried pulling in both directions for the first time.  Pulling the TT's, Spiders and Apes and then pulling the Mares, Jellos and Glares.  It didn't work so well on that raid, but at least he tried and may well have discovered a better way of pulling Fear.<br>
