<br>
Perhaps 72 hours would make more sense.  As it stands now, Vox has been alive much longer than any of us would like.<br>
KILL THE FOUL WURM.<br>
<br>
Oakendar Silverwulf<br>
Druid of the Glade<br>
United Norrathian Brotherhood <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uganaddor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ganaddor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/24/01 7:48:52 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/G36206?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion on Vox rotation....</span><hr size=1> First, we have the experience, but with the 48 hour rule Oakendar and Eanamin (ex-UNB but we still treat him as the same) were not there and I became the only one that know how it should be done. Then I got a call from RL and I must postpone it to Tuesday but it didn't happen.<br>
